snippet.textDisplay:
Beard growing contest by TV celebs for fun and to raise money....

Notice those celebs that are ‘sheltering’ seem to be experimenting with facial hair.

I propose a contest to see who has done the best job.

The end of the contest would be when some predetermined milestone in fight against coronavirus is achieved like, for instance, when WHO announces an approved vaccine.

The winner would be the only TV celeb that can keep his creation, at least for a little while, while everyone else has to shave while on the air.

Voting by phone would be continuous during contest with current tabulation regularly announced on their respective shows.

More importantly.....

each vote would require some sort of donation to a charity to be counted.

This could be a fun one, and I could see TV ads popping up from time to time with current state of celebs faces, asking for votes and donations.

Beard growing contests could become popular with local news anchors, talk show hosts, politicians, governors, YouTube vloggers, and others competing with their peers and raising money.



****



If this proposal sounds like it might be a fun one, please send copy or refer this comment to someone you know that might be in a position to ‘kick it upstairs’ towards others closer to the top of the decision matrix for consideration.

Thank you, and stay healthy.....
